# Understanding basics

If software engineering, don't repeate yourself (DRY) is a principe of software development aimed at reducing repetition of software patterns.

#  Understanding the challenge
Let's assume there are 10 teams in your organization using Terraform to create and manage EC2 instances.

# Better Approach
In this approach, the DevOps Team has defined standart EC2 template in a central location that all can use.

# Intro to T Modules
Terraform Modules allows us to centralize the resource configs and it makes it easier for multiple projects to re-use the Terraform code for projects.

# Multiple Modules for a single project
Insead of writing code from scratch, we can use multiple ready-made modules available.